                  <persName id="t18120916-207-person1606">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18120916-207-person1606" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-207-person1606" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-207-person1606" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Q. What do you know of the loss of these articles - A. I stood at my own door, Mrs. Lawson's little girl said, stop that man, he has taken all the things from my mother's mantle-piece; the prisoner was coming as if from Mrs. Lawson's house. I live at No. 56, <placeName id="t18120916-207-crimeloc1109">Great Saffron-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18120916-207-crimeloc1109" type="placeName" value="Great Saffron-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18120916-207-crimeloc1109" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-207-off1106 t18120916-207-crimeloc1109"></join>; Mrs. Lawson's yard adjoins my house. I stopped the prisoner; he heard the charge of stripping Mrs. Lawson's mantle-piece. Upon searching him I found four shells, two salts, four images; he threw them into a water but.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120916-207-person1607">
                  JOHN 
                  HUTT
               <interp inst="t18120916-207-person1607" type="surname" value="HUTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-207-person1607" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-207-person1607" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner in custody; he confessed the robbery. His master came forward and offered the prosecutrix a pound note to do it away. I was obliged to indict the prisoner myself.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had not the least reason to expect that I should be called upon to answer this charge.</p>
               <p>Q. to Mrs. Brown. Is Mrs. 
